t: To the chief Musician on Neginoth, A Psalm or Song of Asaph.
In*p Judah is God known: his name is great in Israel.
In*p Salem also is his tabernacle, and his dwelling place in Zion.
There*p brake he the arrows of the bow, the shield, and the sword, and the battle. Selah.
Thou*p art more glorious and excellent than the mountains of prey.
The*p stouthearted are spoiled, they have slept their sleep: and none of the men of might have found their hands.
At*p thy rebuke, O God of Jacob, both the chariot and horse are cast into a dead sleep.
Thou,*p even thou, art to be feared: and who may stand in thy sight when once thou art angry?
Thou*p didst cause judgment to be heard from heaven; the earth feared, and was still,
When*p God arose to judgment, to save all the meek of the earth. Selah.
Surely*p the wrath of man shall praise thee: the remainder of wrath shalt thou restrain.
Vow,*p and pay unto the Lord*s your God: let all that be round about him bring presents unto him that ought to be feared.
He*p shall cut off the spirit of princes: he is terrible to the kings of the earth.
